{"id":"327722932_WASP_Write_a_Scientific_Paper_Structuring_a_scientific_paper","abstract":"Writing and publishing scientific papers have become requisites for all scientists (researchers and academics alike) to maintain their professional career. The prospects of writing a scientific paper are often regarded as somewhat daunting to the uninitiated. However a universal, well established structure format known as \"IMRAD\": i.e. Introduction, Methods, Results And Discussion has been established. This paper details this methodology.","authors":["Sarah Cuschieri","Victor Grech","Charles Savona-Ventura"],"meta":["September 2018Early Human Development 128","DOI:10.1016/j.earlhumdev.2018.09.011","Project: WASP - Writing a scientific paper"],"references":["319922552_WASP_-_Write_a_Scientific_Paper_course_why_and_how","286208053_Preferred_Reporting_Items_for_Systematic_Reviews_and_Meta-Analyses_The_PRISMA_Statement","232612229_How_to_write_a_scientific_article","9076071_Towards_Complete_and_Accurate_Reporting_of_Studies_of_Diagnostic_Accuracy_The_STARD_Initiative","323447866_WASP_Is_open_access_publishing_the_way_forward_A_review_of_the_different_ways_in_which_research_papers_can_be_published","322684217_Write_a_scientific_paper_WASP_-_a_career-critical_skill","322385007_How_to_write_a_scientific_paper_-_and_win_the_game_scientists_play","216832104_Some_general_advice_for_writing_a_scientific_paper","11793226_Reasons_Reviewers_Reject_and_Accept_Manuscripts_The_Strengths_and_Weaknesses_in_Medical_Education_Reports","10824673_The_CONSORT_Statement_Revised_Recommendations_for_Improving_the_Quality_of_Reports_of_Parallel-Group_Randomized_Trials","8497161_How_to_write_a_thesis","8267046_The_top_10_reasons_why_manuscripts_are_not_accepted_for_publication"]}